'''Thorn Drumheller''', also known as '''Willow Ufgood''' or '''[[Weazel/Legends|Weazel]]''', was a [[Nelwyn]] from [[Andowyne]].<ref name="Databank" />

{{Char-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
On [[April 1]], [[2006]], as part of an [[Wikipedia:April Fools' Day|April Fools' Day]] joke on [[StarWars.com]], several entries were added to the [[Databank (original)|Databank]] on characters and locations from the film [[Willow (film)|''Willow'']] and its sequel novels, [[Willow (film)#Star Wars connections|''The Shadow War Chronicles'']]. One of these entries identified the character [[Weazel/Legends|Weazel]], played by [[Warwick Davis]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']], as Willow Ufgood, a.k.a. Thorn Drumheller, a character played by Davis in ''Willow''. At [[2005]]'s [[Celebration III]], Warwick Davis explained that people often assume that his Weasel character in ''The Phantom Menace'' is Willow.<ref name="SWArchive-starwars.com at Celebration III - Your Host: Warwick Davis">{{SWArchive|url=community/event/celebration/f20050419/indexp30.html|text=starwars.com at Celebration III - Your Host: Warwick Davis}}</ref>

